SPORTS = [
    {"hero":True,"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Sinner survives bloody five-set scare in Wimbledon opener","summary":"Defending champion Jannik Sinner rallied from two sets to one down to beat Miomir Kecmanovic on Centre Court despite a nasty slip.","body":["Sinner needed five sets to get past Miomir Kecmanovic on the opening day at Wimbledon, prevailing 4-6, 6-3, 6-7, 6-2, 6-3 after a tense battle on Centre Court. The world number one took a heavy fall early in the match that left him with a bloodied foot, briefly raising concern about his fitness before he composed himself and turned the tie around.","Sinner played down the incident afterward, noting that grass courts behave unpredictably in the first days of the tournament. The win keeps the defending champion on track in a half of the draw that also contains Novak Djokovic, setting up a possible semi-final between the pair later in the fortnight."],"sources":[("Olympics.com","https://www.olympics.com/en/news/wimbledon-2026-defending-champion-jannik-sinner-survives-first-round-scare"),("RTE","https://www.rte.ie/sport/tennis/2026/0629/1580936-sinner-bloodied-but-unbowed-in-lengthy-wimbeldon-opener/")]},
    {"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Gauff ends grass losing streak with easy Wimbledon win","summary":"Coco Gauff snapped a four-match grass-court losing run by dispatching Tamara Korpatsch in straight sets on Court 2.","body":["Coco Gauff opened her Wimbledon campaign with a 6-2, 6-1 victory over Germany's Tamara Korpatsch on Court 2, ending a stretch of four straight defeats on grass. The win was a relief for the American, who has struggled to translate her hard-court and clay success onto the surface.","Gauff next faces Argentina's Solana Sierra in the second round as she chases a long-awaited breakthrough at the All England Club. Fellow contenders Aryna Sabalenka and Jessica Pegula also advanced comfortably on the opening day."],"sources":[("Olympics.com","https://www.olympics.com/en/news/wimbledon-2026-coco-gauff-tamara-korpatsch-round-one-tennis-results")]},
    {"sub":"Tennis","h3":"Rublev crashes out as Safiullin wins all-Russian thriller","summary":"Andrey Rublev fell to compatriot Roman Safiullin in a five-set first-round upset on the opening day at Wimbledon.","body":["Roman Safiullin pulled off one of the opening-day surprises at Wimbledon, beating fellow Russian Andrey Rublev 6-4, 6-7, 6-3, 3-6, 7-6 in a marathon five-setter. The deciding tiebreak settled a tie that swung back and forth across more than three hours.","Elsewhere among the men, Daniil Medvedev and Tommy Paul advanced in straight sets, while Joao Fonseca continued his rise with a clean win. The early exit for Rublev opens up that quarter of the draw for the seeds who progressed."],"sources":[("ESPN","https://www.espn.com/tennis/story/_/id/49213777/wimbledon-2026-today-blog-29-06-2026-tennis-live-updates-news-fixtures-schedule-results-aryna-sabalenka-jannik-sinner"),("Sky Sports","https://www.skysports.com/tennis/news/32498/13557566/wimbledon-2026-mens-draw-schedule-results-including-jack-draper-jannik-sinner-and-novak-djokovic")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Paraguay stun Germany on penalties in World Cup last 32","summary":"Paraguay knocked four-time champions Germany out of the 2026 World Cup in a penalty shootout in Boston.","body":["Paraguay produced the biggest shock of the Round of 32 so far, eliminating Germany on penalties at Gillette Stadium near Boston. After the sides could not be separated in normal time, the South Americans held their nerve from the spot to send one of the tournament favorites home early.","The result reshapes the knockout bracket and continues a difficult campaign for Germany, who arrived among the contenders. Paraguay march on into the Round of 16 with momentum on their side."],"sources":[("Yahoo Sports","https://sports.yahoo.com/soccer/live/world-cup-2026-scores-results-schedule-live-updates-round-of-32-173000083.html")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Brazil ease past Japan to reach World Cup last 16","summary":"Brazil overcame Japan at NRG Stadium in Houston to book their place in the Round of 16.","body":["Brazil got the better of Japan at NRG Stadium in Houston to advance from the Round of 32 at the 2026 World Cup. The five-time champions controlled the tie and showed the attacking quality that has made them one of the tournament's standout sides.","With the win, Brazil move into the last 16 as one of the favorites to lift the trophy at North America's expanded 48-team tournament. Japan exit after another spirited campaign."],"sources":[("Yahoo Sports","https://sports.yahoo.com/soccer/live/world-cup-2026-scores-results-schedule-live-updates-round-of-32-173000083.html")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Netherlands meet Morocco in heavyweight last-32 clash","summary":"The Netherlands faced Morocco in Monterrey in one of the standout Round of 32 fixtures of the World Cup.","body":["The Netherlands took on Morocco at Estadio BBVA in Monterrey in a heavyweight Round of 32 meeting between two of the tournament's most watched sides. The Dutch advanced to the knockout phase as winners of Group F, setting up the clash with a Morocco team that has built a reputation as a serious contender.","Both nations carried strong squads into the knockout rounds, making the tie one of the most anticipated of the round. A place in the Round of 16 was on the line in Mexico."],"sources":[("ESPN","https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/49220087/netherlands-morocco-live-world-cup-2026-latest-updates-commentary-score-result"),("Al Jazeera","https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/6/29/netherlands-vs-morocco-fifa-world-cup-round-of-32-prediction-team-news")]},
    {"sub":"Football","h3":"Ajax brace for major squad overhaul as window opens","summary":"Technical director Jordi Cruijff is reportedly ready to move on up to fifteen players as the Dutch summer window heats up.","body":["Ajax are bracing for a busy summer, with reports that technical director Jordi Cruijff is willing to part with as many as fifteen players. Wout Weghorst is on his way out, Chuba Akpom has already left and Kasper Dolberg is expected to follow.","On the incoming side, Brazilian international Henrique chose the Johan Cruijff Arena over interest from England and Italy. Rivals PSV and Feyenoord are also hunting strikers, with Ricardo Pepi tipped to leave Eindhoven and Ayase Ueda linked with a move away from Rotterdam."],"sources":[("Ajax Showtime","https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/bijzaken-en-geruchten/markt-open-transfers-zomer-2026-eredivisie-op-een-rij"),("NL Times","https://nltimes.nl/2026/01/01/january-transfer-window-opens-big-decisions-looming-psv-ajax-feyenoord")]},
    {"sub":"Formula 1","h3":"Russell ends winless run with Austrian GP victory","summary":"George Russell held off Max Verstappen to win the Austrian Grand Prix and reignite his title bid.","body":["George Russell converted pole position into victory at the Austrian Grand Prix, finishing just over a second clear of Max Verstappen after a tense second half of the race. Kimi Antonelli completed the podium in third as Russell ended a winless stretch.","The result lifted Russell back into second place in the drivers' championship and gave fresh life to his title campaign. Verstappen pushed hard in the closing laps but could not find a way past the Mercedes."],"sources":[("Formula1.com","https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/russell-seals-victory-in-thrilling-austrian-grand-prix-ahead-of-verstappen-and-antonelli.5kjw8LmvWRcsaFgjCr8aWw"),("Sky Sports","https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13558494/austrian-gp-george-russell-holds-off-max-verstappen-to-end-winless-streak-and-reinvigorate-title-bid")]},
    {"sub":"Formula 1","h3":"Russell escapes penalty for yellow-flag pole lap in Austria","summary":"Stewards cleared George Russell over a yellow-flag incident during his pole-winning qualifying lap in Austria.","body":["George Russell avoided an investigation that could have cost him pole position in Austria after a yellow flag was waved during his final qualifying lap. Stewards judged that the marshalling sequence did not require him to lift, allowing his time to stand.","The qualifying session was overshadowed by a dramatic late crash from Max Verstappen, which brought out the yellow flags. Russell beat Charles Leclerc and Lewis Hamilton to top spot on the grid before going on to win the race."],"sources":[("Motorsport.com","https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/why-george-russell-escaped-investigation-for-yellow-flag-austria-f1-pole-lap/10834052/")]},
    {"sub":"Sailing","h3":"Los Gallos claim first SailGP win of the season in Halifax","summary":"Diego Botin's Los Gallos stormed to victory at the Canada Sail Grand Prix, climbing to second in the standings.","body":["Diego Botin and Los Gallos secured their first event win of the 2026 SailGP season at the Canada Sail Grand Prix in Halifax. The result also denied the debutant Artemis team a shot at their first ever SailGP victory.","The win lifted Los Gallos above Emirates GBR into second place in the championship standings on 44 points. Tom Slingsby's BONDS Flying Roos remain top of the table on 62 points as the global league rolls on."],"sources":[("SailGP","https://sailgp.com/betting/tips/canada-sail-grand-prix-recap-los-gallos-sailgp-teams-storms-to-halifax-win")]},
    {"sub":"BJJ & Judo","h3":"Pato breaks lightweight title record at IBJJF Worlds","summary":"Diego Pato Oliveira became the most decorated light featherweight in history at the 30th IBJJF World Championship.","body":["Diego Oliveira, known as Pato, was the standout performer at the 30th IBJJF World Championship in Long Beach, becoming the winningest light featherweight in the sport's history. He surpassed the record of four world titles held by his own coach, Guilherme Mendes.","The adult black belt division produced 335 matches in total, with 115 ending by submission. The milestone caps a remarkable run for one of the division's defining grapplers."],"sources":[("FloGrappling","https://www.flograppling.com/articles/15951418-ibjjf-worlds-2026-results-heres-every-division-winner"),("BJJ Heroes","https://www.bjjheroes.com/bjj-news/ibjjf-world-championship-2026-results")]},
    {"sub":"BJJ & Judo","h3":"ADCC 2026 heads to Krakow as trials wrap up","summary":"The grappling world looks ahead to the ADCC World Championships in Poland, with the qualifying roster taking shape.","body":["The 2026 ADCC World Championships are set for September 12 and 13 in Krakow, Poland, and the field is firming up as the spring and summer trials conclude. The West Coast Trials and South American Trials have already handed out invites to the sport's rising names.","Mayssa Bastos was among the standout trial winners to lock in her place at the no-gi showpiece. With the invite list filling out, attention now turns to the matchups that will define the year's biggest grappling event."],"sources":[("FloGrappling","https://www.flograppling.com/"),("ADCC Official","https://adcc-official.com/")]},
]

